HEADWORD: Kathetal
<hw>Kath"e*tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
perpendicular line. See <er>Cathetus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>Making a right angle; perpendicular, as two lines or two sides of a
triangle, which include a right angle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

